name: The Sky Is Crying
comments: There is confusion about the credits.  On the one hand BMI and APRA credit the song to James/Lewis/Robinson.  On the other hand EMI and HFA credit it to James/Lewis/Levy.

name: Cocaine Blues
comments: T.J. Arnall was a band member of "Slumber Nichols' Western Aces".  We're not 100% sure this is the first version of "Cocaine Blues", there is also a 1947 version by Billy Hughes (King 636) and Roy Hogsed (Coast 262).

name: Transfusion Blues
comments: This cover is credited to Roy Hogsed, which we think is a mistake.  The confusion is probably due to the fact that Roy Hogsed had a little hit with a cover version of "Cocaine Blues".  Finally, note that the song was renamed "Transfusion Blues" because cocaine was taboo.  Interestingly, when Johnny Cash released this song under the original title "Cocaine Blues" on Johnny Cash at Folsom Prison in 1968, it was again credited to T.J. Arnall.
